  "title": "Senior Mechanical Engineer (Quality Control)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<p><br>\nThe role involves overseeing quality assurance and control for ACMV and mechanical works, ensuring all installations and materials meet project specifications, industry standards, and regulatory requirements.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>· Implement and manage quality control procedures for ACMV and mechanical works.</p>\n<p>· Conduct inspections, audits, and testing of materials, equipment, and site installations.</p>\n<p>· Review and verify shop drawings, material submittals, and method statements for compliance.</p>\n<p>· Monitor and ensure workmanship meets design specifications and quality standards.</p>\n<p>· Prepare non-conformance reports (NCRs), corrective action requests, and follow up until closure.</p>\n<p>· Liaise with consultants, clients, and subcontractors to resolve quality-related issues.</p>\n<p>· Maintain quality documentation, inspection reports, and test records.</p>\n<p>· Support handover and commissioning by ensuring all quality requirements are fulfilled.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>· Degree/Diploma in Mechanical Engineering, Building Services, or related discipline.</p>\n<p>· At least 6–8 years of experience in quality control for ACMV/mechanical works in large-scale construction projects.</p>\n<p>· Strong knowledge of ACMV systems, mechanical equipment, and QA/QC procedures.</p>\n<p>· Familiarity with relevant codes, standards, and authority requirements in Singapore.</p>\n<p>· Detail-oriented with strong analytical and problem-solving skills.</p>\n<p>· Good communication and coordination skills to work with multiple stakeholders.</p>\n<p>· Experience with large industrial or infrastructure projects is preferred.</p>\n<p>· Willingness to work at Tuas with transportation pick up at designated MRT station.</p>",
